A weathered farmer in a sun-drenched field, standing at a crossroads between two garden plots viewed from above in warm golden hour light. One plot shows lush, mature fruit trees with diminishing harvests, some branches picked nearly bare. The other plot contains freshly tilled dark soil with small seedlings just beginning to sprout. The farmer holds a watering can, body turned toward the established trees but gaze directed thoughtfully at the young seedlings. Vintage agricultural illustration style with muted earthy tones, crosshatched shading, and the nostalgic quality of 1940s farming almanac artwork. Soft cream and amber color palette with touches of forest green. Bird's eye perspective showing the clear division between immediate abundance and future potential.
